==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crœsus
<hw>Cr⟦oe⟧"sus</hw> <pr>(kr⟦emac⟧"s⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[L., fr. G. <grk>Kroi^sos</grk>.]</ety> <def>A king of Lydia who
flourished in the 6th century <sc>b. c.</sc>, and was renowned for his
vast wealth; hence, a common appellation for a very rich man; <as>as, he
is a veritable <ex>Cr⟦oe⟧sus</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Croft</ent>⟦br⟧
